trend_summary: Built form steadily intensified: the northwest logistics/airport zone sprawled, highways were widened, and scattered lots across the eastern neighbourhoods were filled with housing. Tree belts along the river expanded, while the southern forest block stayed intact. Farmland patches almost vanished, yielding a contiguous suburban matrix by the last image.
notable_changes: Large expansion of airport/industrial rooftops and aprons in the northwest quadrant.
Widening and realignment of the main riverside highway and bridge.
Residential infill replaced vacant or agricultural parcels in the east and northeast.
New greenways and riparian vegetation installed along the river edge.
Stable but more clearly delineated forest reserve in the southern sector.
